─── Migration to Blocks-native (optional) ────────────────────────

To make your app "Blocks-native with Amplify as a guest":

1. Move CDK orchestration from amplify/backend.ts to aws-blocks/index.cdk.ts
   - Use BlocksStack.create() instead of BlocksBackend.create()
   - Import Amplify resources into the Blocks stack

2. Replace `npx ampx sandbox` with `npm run sandbox`
   - Blocks sandbox uses CDK directly (no Amplify CLI dependency)

3. Update amplify.yml to use CDK deploy directly:
   backend.phases.build.commands:
     - npx cdk deploy --require-approval never --app="npx tsx -C cdk aws-blocks/index.cdk.ts"

This gives you full control over the CDK stack while keeping
Amplify Hosting for CI/CD and frontend deployment.
